# GPXeditor — repository ignore rules
#
# Three kinds of things live in this file:
#   1. macOS, Xcode, and Swift build/IDE artifacts that should never be committed
#      regardless of repo visibility.
#   2. Personal-data and credential artifacts that must never be committed
#      regardless of repo visibility, per SECURITY.md and D-005.
#   3. Session-handoff scratch files used during development that aren't
#      project deliverables.
# When updating this file, prefer adding patterns over removing them — and
# never relax the credential-block patterns without a SECURITY.md update.

# ─── macOS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?

# ─── Xcode build / IDE state ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# xcuserdata holds per-user UI state: window layouts, breakpoints, scheme
# selections.  Each developer has their own; checking it in causes constant
# spurious diffs.
**/xcuserdata/
**/*.xcuserstate
build/
DerivedData/

# Swift Package Manager local cache (Package.resolved IS committed; D-007).
.swiftpm/
.build/

# Xcode misc
*.moved-aside
*.xccheckout
*.hmap

# ─── Personal data — GPX tracks ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per D-005, real-world GPX recordings may be committed during the private
# development phase ONLY inside GPXEditorTests/Fixtures/, after a fixture-audit
# review (rules in Docs/06_FIXTURES.md).  Anywhere else in the repo — and any
# track on the repo root — is denied by default.  The allow-list below
# re-enables fixtures explicitly.
*.gpx
!GPXEditorTests/Fixtures/*.gpx

# Optional gitignored landing zone for one-off debugging tracks that should
# never be committed.  Create on demand; tracks here remain local-only.
GPXEditorTests/PrivateFixtures/

# ─── Credentials and signing artifacts (NEVER COMMIT — visibility-independent) ─
# These patterns are absolute per SECURITY.md "Personal data" and
# "Code signing and notarization" sections.  Do not relax them when going
# public; they are not visibility-aware.
*.p12
*.cer
*.mobileprovision
*.provisionprofile
notarization-credentials.json
notarization-api-key.p8
AuthKey_*.p8
*.keychain-db

# ─── Session-handoff scratch files (this development workflow only) ─────────
# These are personal session-handoff notes used between Claude Code sessions
# and are not part of the project deliverable.
Cowork-Session-Handoff.md
StartingPrompt-ClaudeCode.txt

# ─── Auto-generated build identifiers ───────────────────────────────────────
# GPXEditor/Generated/BuildInfo.swift is rewritten on every build by the
# "Generate BuildInfo" Run Script phase (Scripts/generate_build_info.sh).
# It IS committed once so that PBXFileSystemSynchronizedRootGroup picks it
# up at build-graph construction time on a fresh clone — the first build
# would otherwise omit it from the binary.
#
# Each developer runs once after a fresh clone, to suppress the every-
# build local-modification noise that would otherwise fill `git status`:
#
#     git update-index --skip-worktree GPXEditor/Generated/BuildInfo.swift
#
# The pattern below is documentation-of-intent.  Because the file is
# tracked, the gitignore rule is inert — `--skip-worktree` is what
# actually does the noise suppression.  The pattern still catches any
# *other* file that ever lands under a Generated/ subfolder.
**/Generated/BuildInfo.swift

# ─── Claude Code per-developer state ─────────────────────────────────────────
# .claude/settings.json (when present) is project-tracked and contains the
# shared allow/deny rules that constrain unattended `claude -p` runs — see
# CLAUDE.md "Workflow".  .claude/settings.local.json is per-developer and
# accumulates personal command approvals; it stays local.
.claude/settings.local.json
